	<td class="alt1" id="td_post_1173817">
	
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_1173817">
                  
                  <div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				<div>Originally Posted by <strong>jhorry</strong></div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">
<br />
<br />
<br />
Here is my counterspell system change i posted a while back though, so you dont have to serch for it lol:<br />
<br />
<br />
In an ideal world, here is a system for counter spelling i would hope they could implement w/in the next 5 months:<br />
<br />
<br />
Change the UI to better support spell identification.<br />
<br />
It would have a 3-check system for Spell Identification, the higher your skill, the higher the chance that more information would be avalible:<br />
<br />
<b>Check 1</b>: If successful, shows that a spell is being cast, icon is a &quot; ? &quot;<br />
This requires very little Spell ID, and most rolls will almost allways show this.<br />
<br />
All this does is it lets you know a spell is being cast.<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Check 2</b>: If successful, shows the icon and type of the spell being cast, default positioning would be directly above the spell counter icon.<br />
This would be a common sight with average, maxed spell ID, roughly 90% success rate. Would list heal, debuff, damage, or other.<br />
<br />
This lets you know what school of spell is being cast, and with sorcerers, allows them to open up specific counter-chains after countering this spell.<br />
<br />
Example:<br />
<br />
Evocation: damage coming from caster, such as sending a bolt of energy<br />
<br />
Restoration: healing and curing<br />
<br />
Conjuration: summoning minions or projectile damage like summoning arcane daggers to fly at your foe<br />
<br />
Abjuration: debuffs generally<br />
<br />
These would have specific icons for each school, and this was my shorthand list of the spell schools i know i missed a few.<br />
<br />
<b>Check 3</b>: If successful, shows detailed information, such as the spell's name, damage or ammount healed, or a discription of a debuff/buff. Information would be brief but potient, this would be a &quot;hard to get&quot; roll, maybe only 20% chance at normal spell ID, but chance would improve quickly the higher you surpassed the base cap via gear or buffs.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
And this is all logical. It basically is like a moodel of real perception, initial level is the stimulation, the realization that something is happening. Its like looking at a book. The process goes: &quot;i see a visual object&quot; as check one, check two would be &quot;this object is a book&quot;, and check 3 would be &quot;ah, that is The Count of Monty Cristo, a wonderful tale!&quot;<br />
<br />
Imagine that with spell casting. &quot;oh, he's casting!&quot;, &quot;oh crap, its a heal!&quot; and finally, if lucky &quot;ah, he is casting Grand Restoration, which will heal him a great ammount!&quot;<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Now, if they have the ability to seperate the &quot;schools&quot; of spells, then, if they want to get creative (laugh), they could make counter spell triggered abilities, that varry depending on what &quot;school&quot; of spell you countered.<br />
<br />
Counter a heal? Turn it into damage for the heal's original target after you counter it. Or drain the foe's mana worth 3 times the heal's power cost and take some of this mana for your own. Or silence that little jerk from casting any more heals. Or &quot;store&quot; this countered heal and use it later when you chose.<br />
<br />
See, i hope some day we can get a system with options like that avlablible, that would make for some really interesting game play and strategies.<br />
<br />
A &quot;good&quot; sorcerer might deal a tremendous more ammount of damage by counter spelling creatively than a sorcerer that just nuke-spaming and ignoring his countering completely.<br />
<br />
I hope countering can become &quot;dps adventageous&quot; so that it is encouraged by the gameplay.<br />
<br />
<br />
Utility that helps the sorcerer deal more damage makes the game more enjoyable imo, rather than the sorcerer simply dealing damage. You could burn down the healer mobs as it continues to heal itself, or you could counter it and nuke it with its own heal.<br />
<br />
Malicious! <img src="images/smilies/biggrin.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Big Grin" class="inlineimg" /><br />
<br />
<br />
---------------------------------------------<br />
<br />
<br />
Also, as i re-read this, they would need to make foes energy pools finant, instead if infinant, and they would require energy costs for their spells / certain special abilities, which they should have anyway if this is already not the case.<br />
<br />
Infinant energy pools is SO old school eq1 lazy if the devs did that!!<br />
<br />
<br />
But yea, counter spelling could be a good way to add in some VERY strong extra situtational damage, debuffing, energy drain/restoring, and other fun stuff for sorcerers.<br />
<br />
Also, i dont know how it is at the end game, but caster foes should be squishy but devistatingly poweful with their spells.<br />
<br />
A sorcerer's spell defense should be just as much of a wanted comadity as their dps, or a druids healing, or a psionicist's CC.<br />
<br />
All casters will have counter spell, but a sorcerer should be vastly suprieror to any caster against another caster, that is not what a psionicist should be doing hehe.<br />
<br />
<br />
edit:<br />
Actually, after re-reading my final statement, i think it would be better if instead of each caster getting the basic counter spell then a more advanced one later, that the advanced one would be a counter chain like the sorcerer abilities listed above:<br />
<br />
Each of these would have a minute reuse timer.<br />
<br />
The druid's Turn Heal, would become active after blocking a heal or nuke. If a nuke was countered, then using turn heal will heal your defensive target for the nuke's value. If a heal was countered, then the turn heal will damage your offensive target for the heak's value.<br />
<br />
The psionicist's Psychic Mutation would become active after their counter spell, and would turn the spell into energy for the psionicist's defensive target.<br />
<br />
For necromancer's, im not really sure what would be a good counter, a life tap (health to self) on the foe equal to the damage of the blocked nuke?<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Sorcerer would have upwards of 6 or 8 different abilities that they could use, mostly depending on what school of spell they countered, and the sorcerer's would be more powerful.</div>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>
<br />
These are some quite interesting ideas to enhance Counter-Spelling.  It would be interesting to be able to try to take advantage of an opponent's healing or even buffs and to have such options in counter magic warfare.  Plus these would inarguably fit with the arcane caster's theme, especially that of the sorcerer.  <br />
<br />
<br />
The idea of an ice barrier is interesting as are certain changes to  Chromatic Barrier such as a spell identification bonus.  It would perhaps be good however to shift some of these things to concentrations/forms as with higher % effects and the ability to become immune to stun, interruption, and counter-spelling while making a few changes to the barriers/shields themselves.  The basic gist of the ice shield, with certain modifications, could work out nicely.
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
