<br />
Yea if they do make these barriers into our versions of stances, i hope they add some negatives to swaping them constantly, like the large energy cost someone mentioned. This would mean we would want to swap them inbetween fights, but would rarely choose to swap during a fight, and never stance dance, which is something everyone wants to avoid.<br />
<br />
Having suggested some revisions to the Psionicist's Concentrations, i decided our Force Barrier would be better as:<br />
<br />
* Absorbs 1 melee hit every 15 seconds.<br />
* Increases AC by 30%<br />
* AOE damage prevention, but does not prevent the effects of the aoes.<br />
* Immune to being interupted by melee while casting<br />
(but <i>not</i> immune to interuptions from control effects)<br />
<br />
You surround yourself in a sheltering arcane barrier that blocks damage from indirect attacks, and can absorb a physical blow completely, but will take time to regenerate your shield.<br />
<br />
Perfect for soloing when kiting is not an option, or when a foe has a ranged physical attack. Good for grouping and raiding for when you cant range an aoe, or for when you want to be up close and personal to use Shocking Grasp (if they wish to improve it that is)<br />
<br />
<br />
How does that sound?<br />
<br />
The stun from Force Barrier would be moved to the Frost Barrier, either as a reactive shield or a spell proc.<br />
<br />
* Reactive stun for 3 seconds when hit, refreshes every 15 sec.<br />
* 75% damage rune, single trigger that refeshes every 15 sec.<br />
* 25% less hate generation<br />
* 15% chance on spell attacks to snare the foe for 75% for 8 seconds.<br />
<br />
<br />
What this would do, is while using Frost Barrier to solo, you are incased in a barrier of ice. If a foe manages to catch up to you and smack you, this icey barrier absorbs most of the damage and briefly freezes your foe, but this barrier takes time to reform (hince the 15 second wait on it)<br />
<br />
This is the perfect Barrier for kiting while solo, or for avoiding pulling agro / dealing with agro after you pull it while grouped.<br />
<br />
<br />
Chromatic Barrier could be the equivilant to these, but would be focused towards casting.<br />
<br />
* 100% single charge spell shield every 15 seconds<br />
* 100% single charge spell reflect every 60 seconds<br />
* Immunity to Control effects<br />
* Improved spell ID and +50% chance to land counter spells<br />
<br />
If they wanted to make Flame Barrier simular with these 3 then, they could make it have a 15 second refresh +50% damage to next spell cast.<br />
<br />
* +30% single charge spell damage increase on next cast every 15 seconds<br />
* Increases energy regeneration<br />
* Adds a fiery damage shield and heat resistance to group<br />
* 15% chance to return energy with each cast
                  
